(10, 1, '2012-02-14 14:31:22', '2012-02-14 19:31:22', '<h1>Back to Our Roots Community Garden</h1>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society proudly sponsors an annual community garden (April-October) located in the town of Chapeau next to Harrington Hall (see map) As an agricultural society we encourage locally grown produce, heritage seed use and the involvement of all members of our community, year round and seasonal residents.\r\n\r\nIf you wish to rent a plot at the garden, please read the Terms and Conditions, complete the Rental Agreement and contact our Community Garden coordinator, Mr. Eddy Schmidt at 819-689-1008\r\n\r\nOr    <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="mailto:beyondnutrition@nrtco.net">beyondnutrition@nrtco.net</a></span>', 'Community Gardens', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'community-gardens', '', '', '2012-03-29 18:53:09', '2012-03-29 18:53:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wilk0146/chapeau/?page_id=10', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(12, 1, '2012-02-14 14:31:33', '2012-02-14 19:31:33', '<h1>Education</h1>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society has as one of its renewal objectives to provide educational activities to our members and the local community that will enhance the quality of agriculture.  To this end, we have identified five initiatives for development; a renewed 4H club, an annual public lecture series, an annual workshop series, organized tours/trips and agricultural exchanges both national and international.\r\n\r\nThis is an ambitious multi-year objective and will need considerable support.', 'Education', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'education', '', '', '2012-03-29 19:00:54', '2012-03-29 19:00:54', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wilk0146/chapeau/?page_id=12', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(14, 1, '2012-02-14 14:31:56', '2012-02-14 19:31:56', '<h1 style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Just For Fun</strong></h1>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h3>Pumpkin Contest</h3>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society is sponsoring a pumpkin growing contest for all residents of the Upper Pontiac. There will be three age groups: 8 and under, 9-17, 18 and over. The society is donating 200 seeds to challenge young growers as part of their school curriculum. Seeds will be distributed through the schools. The Society will hold an open workshop at Harrington Hall on Saturday April 21<sup>st</sup> from 10 am until 12 noon for anyone wishing to learn more about growing pumpkins in the Pontiac. Local food vendors and music will be on hand in the afternoon of the judging, Saturday October 6<sup>th</sup>. Judging will take place at 2 p.m. Good luck to all!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>  Rules:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li> To be eligible, pumpkins must be grown in the Upper Pontiac.</li>\r\n	<li>Contestants may enter pumpkins in one age category. The three age categories are: 8 and under, 9-17 and 18 and over.</li>\r\n	<li>Eligible pumpkins will be judged by weight alone.</li>\r\n	<li>The judges will be the authorities in all matters.</li>\r\n	<li>Prizes for each category will be awarded as follows: ribbons for all participants, ribbons for 1<sup>st</sup>, 2<sup>nd</sup> and 3<sup>rd</sup> prizes in each category, cash prizes of $50 for each first place winner. The winner must be present to win.</li>\r\n	<li>Pumpkins must be delivered and registered between 10 a.m. and noon  on Saturday October 6<sup>th</sup> at Harrington Hall.</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation and loading/unloading of the pumpkins is the responsibility of the entrants.</li>\r\n	<li>Pumpkins must be left on display until 5 p.m. Pumpkins remaining after that time will be donated with thanks to the community garden compost pile.</li>\r\n	<li>The grower must agree  to donate 50 seeds from winning pumpkins if asked to further promote the Chapeau Agricultural Society Pumpkin Contest.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrants are free to use any pumpkin seed. The Society will provide seeds to all school aged children in the upper Pontiac.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Just For Fun', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fun', '', '', '2012-03-29 18:46:49', '2012-03-29 18:46:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wilk0146/chapeau/?page_id=14', 0, 'page', '', 0),
