(241, 2, '2012-03-28 00:47:06', '2012-03-28 00:47:06', '<h1 style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Just For Fun</strong></h1>\n<h2>Pumpkin Contest</h2>\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society is sponsoring a pumpkin growing contest for all residents of the Upper Pontiac. There will be three age groups: 8 and under, 9-17, 18 and over. The society is donating 200 seeds to challenge young growers as part of their school curriculum. Seeds will be distributed through the schools. The Society will hold an open workshop at Harrington Hall on Saturday April 21<sup>st</sup> from 10 am until 12 noon for anyone wishing to learn more about growing pumpkins in the Pontiac. Local food vendors and music will be on hand in the afternoon of the judging, Saturday October 6<sup>th</sup>. Judging will take place at 2 p.m. Good luck to all!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><strong>Rules:</strong></h3>\n&nbsp;\n\n1. To be eligible, pumpkins must be grown in the Upper Pontiac.\n\n2. Contestants may enter pumpkins in one age category. The three age categories are: 8 and under, 9-17 and 18 and over.\n\n3. Eligible pumpkins will be judged by weight alone.\n\n4. The judges will be the authorities in all matters.\n\n5. Prizes for each category will be awarded as follows: ribbons for all participants, ribbons for 1<sup>st</sup>, 2<sup>nd</sup> and 3<sup>rd</sup> prizes in each category, cash prizes of $50 for each first place winner. The winner must be present to win.\n\n6. Pumpkins must be delivered and registered between 10 a.m. and noon  on Saturday October 6<sup>th</sup> at Harrington Hall.\n\n7. Transportation and loading/unloading of the pumpkins is the responsibility of the entrants.\n\n8. Pumpkins must be left on display until 5 p.m. Pumpkins remaining after that time will be donated with thanks to the community garden compost pile.\n\n9. The grower must agree  to donate 50 seeds from winning pumpkins if asked to further promote the Chapeau Agricultural Society Pumpkin Contest.\n\n10. Entrants are free to use any pumpkin seed. The Society will provide seeds to all school aged children in the upper Pontiac.', 'Just For Fun', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-autosave', '', '', '2012-03-28 00:47:06', '2012-03-28 00:47:06', '', 14, 'http://chapeau.phpfogapp.com/2012/03/14-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(242, 2, '2012-03-08 22:45:51', '2012-03-08 22:45:51', 'This is the Membership page\n\nOur members are our strength and over the years we have had the benefit of many highly motivated and dedicated members from all our local communities.\n\nMembership is open to anyone who accepts the mission of the Society and who is prepared, on a volunteer basis, to contribute responsibly to the work of the Society.\n\nThe annual membership fee is $10.00 payable by cheque or cash to the Treasurer.\n\nPlease print the following Membership Form and send it, with your membership fee, to the Treasurer.\n<ul>\n	<li>Mr. Louis Lair</li>\n	<li>Treasurer</li>\n	<li>Chapeau Agricultural Society</li>\n	<li>C.P./P.O. Box 176</li>\n	<li>Chapeau, QC</li>\n	<li>Canada</li>\n	<li>J0X 1M0</li>\n</ul>\n<a title="Membership Application Form PDF" href="forms/ApplicationForm.pdf">Membership Application Form PDF</a>\n\nRight-click the link to the PDF file, and then choose Save Target As from the pop-up menu.', 'Membership', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '55-autosave', '', '', '2012-03-08 22:45:51', '2012-03-08 22:45:51', '', 55, 'http://chapeau.phpfogapp.com/2012/03/55-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(248, 2, '2012-03-08 22:22:48', '2012-03-08 22:22:48', '<p>This is the About Us page</p>\r\n<p>The Chapeau Agricultural Society is comprised of an enthusiastic and diverse collection of individuals and farmers who are passionate about agriculture in our community; the Upper Pontiac region of the province of Quebec.  We are a non-profit organization celebrating 134 years of service in 2012.  The Society is revitalizing itself to match the changing dynamic of farming today within a rural community that includes a growing number of ex-urbanites.</p>\r\n', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '63-revision-3', '', '', '2012-03-08 22:22:48', '2012-03-08 22:22:48', '', 63, 'http://chapeau.phpfogapp.com/2012/03/63-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
