(374, 2, '2012-03-29 18:51:36', '2012-03-29 18:51:36', '<h1>Back to Our Roots Community Garden</h1>\n<h2> Introduction</h2>\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society proudly sponsors an annual community garden (April-October) located in the town of Chapeau next to Harrington Hall (see map) As an agricultural society we encourage locally grown produce, heritage seed use and the involvement of all members of our community, year round and seasonal residents.\n\nIf you wish to rent a plot at the garden, please read the Terms and Conditions, complete the Rental Agreement and contact our Community Garden coordinator, Mr. Eddy Schmidt at 819-689-1008\n\nOr    <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="mailto:beyondnutrition@nrtco.net">beyondnutrition@nrtco.net</a></span>\n<h2> Location</h2>\n(To be provided)\n\nMap of region and Chapeau, Harrington Hall\n\nDiagram of available numbered plots and parking\n<h2> Season, Hours</h2>\n8am to 8pm, seven days a week during the months of April through October\n\nEach renter will be provided with a garden gate key for individual access during this period.  Please return your key at the end of the season to the suggestion box next to the Noticeboard at the Garden.\n<h2> Terms and Conditions</h2>\n<ul>\n	<li>Each renter is a current member of the Chapeau Agricultural Society</li>\n	<li>The Chapeau Agricultural Society will provide each renter with one numbered plot for the season, the rental fee will be determined by the size of the plot and clearly noted on the rental agreement.</li>\n	<li>Each renter is responsible for the continual maintenance of their plot for the duration of the rental period.</li>\n	<li>Garbage cans, composters and a tool shed will be provided for renter use. Please use composters for all weeds, unwanted vegetation</li>\n	<li>Parking is free and picnicking is encouraged</li>\n	<li>A Noticeboard will be maintained by the Chapeau Agricultural Society for any important gardening and or society information.</li>\n	<li>The Chapeau Agricultural Society is not liable for any theft or injury on its property, including the   community garden.</li>\n	<li>Behaviour while in the community garden is guided by the honour system with everyone expected to respect the hard work and produce of everyone else.</li>\n	<li>In accordance with municipal and provincial law, no alcoholic beverages or drugs are allowed in the community garden.</li>\n	<li>At the end of the season, all unclaimed produce will be donated to charity or composted.</li>\n	<li>- All renters must follow the tenants of organic gardening, for direction please contact the community garden coordinator.</li>\n	<li>Signing the rental agreement means that the renter agrees with and will abide by all the terms and conditions listed here.</li>\n</ul>\n<a href="http://loclhost/chapeau/forms/Community Garden Plot Rental Form.pdf">Back to Our Roots Community Garden Rental Agreement (PDF)</a>\n<h2>Back to Our Roots Workshops</h2>\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society will provide at least two public workshops for local gardeners and Community Garden renters each season.  The topics will focus on practical methods for successful garden crops in our locale and will include questions and answers.  The workshop leaders will usually be from the Society board but other gardeners may be invited to share their experience and expertise.\n\nThe workshop schedule will be posted on the Noticeboard at the Community Gardens, on this website and depending on numbers of participants in the local media.\n\nIf you have any suggestions or would like to volunteer as a workshop leader please contact Mr. Eddy Schmidt, our Community Garden coordinator at 819-689-1008 or <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="mailto:beyondnutrition@nrtco.net">beyondnutrition@nrtco.net</a></span>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Community Gardens', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '10-autosave', '', '', '2012-03-29 18:51:36', '2012-03-29 18:51:36', '', 10, 'http://localhost/chapeau/2012/03/10-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
