(429, 2, '2012-03-28 00:46:04', '2012-03-28 00:46:04', '<h1 style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Just For Fun</strong></h1>\r\n<h2>Pumpkin Contest</h2>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society is sponsoring a pumpkin growing contest for all residents of the Upper Pontiac. There will be three age groups: 8 and under, 9-17, 18 and over. The society is donating 200 seeds to challenge young growers as part of their school curriculum. Seeds will be distributed through the schools. The Society will hold an open workshop at Harrington Hall on Saturday April 21<sup>st</sup> from 10 am until 12 noon for anyone wishing to learn more about growing pumpkins in the Pontiac. Local food vendors and music will be on hand in the afternoon of the judging, Saturday October 6<sup>th</sup>. Judging will take place at 2 p.m. Good luck to all!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Rules:</strong></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n1. To be eligible, pumpkins must be grown in the Upper Pontiac.\r\n\r\n2. Contestants may enter pumpkins in one age category. The three age categories are: 8 and under, 9-17 and 18 and over.\r\n\r\n3. Eligible pumpkins will be judged by weight alone.\r\n\r\n4. The judges will be the authorities in all matters.\r\n\r\n5. Prizes for each category will be awarded as follows: ribbons for all participants, ribbons for 1<sup>st</sup>, 2<sup>nd</sup> and 3<sup>rd</sup> prizes in each category, cash prizes of $50 for each first place winner. The winner must be present to win.\r\n\r\n6. Pumpkins must be delivered and registered between 10 a.m. and noon  on Saturday October 6<sup>th</sup> at Harrington Hall.\r\n\r\n7. Transportation and loading/unloading of the pumpkins is the responsibility of the entrants.\r\n\r\n8. Pumpkins must be left on display until 5 p.m. Pumpkins remaining after that time will be donated with thanks to the community garden compost pile.\r\n\r\n9. The grower must agree  to donate 50 seeds from winning pumpkins if asked to further promote the Chapeau Agricultural Society Pumpkin Contest.\r\n\r\n10. Entrants are free to use any pumpkin seed. The Society will provide seeds to all school aged children in the upper Pontiac.', 'Just For Fun', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '14-revision-7', '', '', '2012-03-28 00:46:04', '2012-03-28 00:46:04', '', 14, 'http://chapeau.phpfogapp.com/2012/03/14-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(430, 2, '2012-03-27 23:04:23', '2012-03-27 23:04:23', '<h1>Education</h1>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society has as one of its renewal objectives to provide educational activities to our members and the local community that will enhance the quality of agriculture.  To this end, we have identified five initiatives for development; a renewed 4H club, an annual public lecture series, an annual workshop series, organized tours/trips and agricultural exchanges both national and international.\r\n\r\nThis is an ambitious multi-year objective and will need considerable support.\r\n<h2>4H</h2>\r\nCurrently we are looking for an adult who would be willing to act as 4H leader in our area. The Quebec4H is a well established organization with sponsorship resources to provide it’s young members, ages 6 to 25 with a full program of activities. Go to <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://quebec4h.com/">http://quebec4h.com</a></span> for an excellent introduction to the organization.\r\n\r\nAll we need is a leader and a minimum of 5 members to start our own Upper Pontiac 4H club.\r\n\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society would like to support 4H in our community as a local sponsor and partner.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested or know of someone who might be interested in getting a 4H club started please contact any of our board members listed on this website.\r\n<h2>Lectures</h2>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society intends to host a minimum of two public lectures each year on topics of interest to area farmers and those supporting farmers.\r\n\r\nThe lectures will be open to the public and held in Harrington Hall in Chapeau, a small fee will be charged for non members, members can attend for free, memberships will be on sale at each lecture.\r\n\r\nIf you have any suggestions for lecture topics, please contact any of our board members listed on this website.\r\n<h2>Workshops</h2>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society will establish an annual series of workshops on specific topics to assist practicing farmers and their families.  For example, farm management software, farm tax accounting, herd management, investment strategies for farmers, farmers and bankers.\r\n\r\nIf you, as a practicing farmer, have any suggestions for our workshop series, please contact any of our board members listed on this website.\r\n<h2>Tours/Trips</h2>\r\nThe Chapeau Agricultural Society will assist both tours of local farms/producers for visitors or will assist with trips to other points of interest for local farmers/producers who wish to learn more about agricultural practice.\r\n\r\nAgritours Canada is a national organization that provides both inbound tours for foreign agriculture groups and outbound international tours for Canadian farmers and agricultural groups. Learn more about these opportunities at <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.agritourscanada.com/">www.agritourscanada.com</a></span>\r\n\r\nIf you think we can be of assistance please contact any of the society directors listed in this website.\r\n<h2>Exchange Programs</h2>\r\nAgricultural exchange programs support farmers worldwide.  We have listed two programs that may be of interest to your farm either as a host farm or perhaps you have a young farmer who wants to see the world.\r\n<h2>International Rural Exchange</h2>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.irecanada.ca/">www.irecanada.ca</a></span>\r\n\r\nPhone  306-489-4407\r\n\r\nFAX    306-489-4607\r\n\r\nAlameda, Saskatchewan, Canada, S0C 0A0, Box 367\r\n\r\nEmail  <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="mailto:info@irecanada.ca">info@irecanada.ca</a></span>\r\n<h2>Agriventure  International Rural Placements</h2>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.agriventure.com/">www.agriventure.com</a></span>\r\n<h2>Agriventure Global Canadian Office</h2>\r\nNE 26-38-21  W2\r\n\r\nSt. Peter’s Rm#369\r\n\r\nBox 165, Annaheim\r\n\r\nSaskatchewan, Canada, S0K 0G0\r\n\r\n1-888-598-4415\r\n\r\nEmail <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="mailto:allison@agriventure.com">allison@agriventure.com</a></span>', 'Education', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '12-revision-9', '', '', '2012-03-27 23:04:23', '2012-03-27 23:04:23', '', 12, 'http://chapeau.phpfogapp.com/2012/03/12-revision-9/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
